Package com.postman.collection

Class PostmanResponse

java.lang.Object
com.postman.collection.PostmanCollectionElement
com.postman.collection.PostmanResponse
public class PostmanResponse extends PostmanCollectionElement
Class to encapsulate the response object property of a PostmanItem A PostmanRequest includes an optional array of expected responses: 
  "response": [
                {
                    "name": "NORMAL Urlencoded",
                    "originalRequest": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "https://postman-echo.com/post",
                            "host": [
                                "postman-echo",
                                "com"
                            ],
                            "path": [
                                "post"
                            ],
                            "protocol": "https"
                        },
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "urlencoded",
                            "urlencoded": [
                                {
                                    "key": "x-field-2",
                                    "value": "value 2",
                                    "description": "This is value 2"
                                },
                                {
                                    "key": "x-field-1",
                                    "value": "value 1",
                                    "description": "This is value 1"
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    },
                    "code": 200,
                    "status": "OK",
                    "_postman_previewlanguage": "",
                    "body": "this is the expected response body"
                }
            ]
The response object includes a PostmanRequest object describing the original request associated with this response.
